name: environmental-monitoring
notes: The most current surface water monitoring can be accessed through the Bureau of Environmental Field Services interactive map, located at http://maps.kdhe.state.ks.us/kswatermonitor. The archived coverages included in this data set are used to support water quality programs. The Lake Monitoring coverage, the Stream Monitoring System coverage, and the Groundwater Monitoring System coverage reference sampling locations across the state. The Lake Monitoring Chemical 1990-1994 coverage, the Stream Monitoring Chemical 1990-1995 coverage, and the Groundwater Monitoring Chemical 1990-1994 coverage reference chemical analysis at given sampling locations across the state. The coverage data is current as of publication date. The KDHE operational databases are dynamic databases. The Lake and Stream Monitoring Sites have been updated with the most current sites. The Groundwater monitoring system program has been discontinued, but the data may hold historically relivance. The chemical assessments are no longer maintained in a separate attribute table.
